---
// src/pages/reviews/pixel-10-pro-review.astro
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Google Pixel 10 Pro Review 2026 - The Smartest Phone Yet?">
  <article class="review">
    <header class="review-header">
      <span class="category">Google</span>
      <h1>Google Pixel 10 Pro Review: The Smartest AI Phone Yet?</h1>
      <div class="meta">
        <span>By Alice AI</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>March 11, 2026</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="rating">
      <span class="score">4.7</span>
      <span class="stars">⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐</span>
    </div>

    <div class="toc">
      <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="#overview">Overview</a></li>
        <li><a href="#ai-features">Magic of Gemini 2.0</a></li>
        <li><a href="#camera">Pro Camera System</a></li>
        <li><a href="#performance">Tensor G5 Evolution</a></li>
        <li><a href="#battery">Power Management</a></li>
        <li><a href="#verdict">Verdict</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>The Pixel 10 Pro marks a decade of Google's hardware journey, and it's their most ambitious effort yet. With the fully custom Tensor G5 chip and deeply integrated Gemini 2.0 AI, it moves beyond being just a smartphone to a true personal assistant.</p>
      
      <div class="pros-cons">
        <div class="pros">
          <h3>Pros</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>✅ Unrivaled AI integration with Gemini 2.0</li>
            <li>✅ Best-in-class computational photography</li>
            <li>✅ First true custom Tensor G5 performance boost</li>
            <li>✅ 7 years of guaranteed OS updates</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="cons">
          <h3>Cons</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>❌ AI features still require high data usage</li>
            <li>❌ Charging speed lags behind competitors</li>
            <li>❌ Design is iterative rather than revolutionary</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="ai-features">
      <h2>Magic of Gemini 2.0</h2>
      <p>The Pixel 10 Pro is built around Gemini 2.0. From real-time voice translation that sounds human to "Magic Eraser Video" that can remove unwanted objects from 4K footage, the AI processing happens almost entirely on-device thanks to the new NPU in the Tensor G5.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="camera">
      <h2>Pro Camera System</h2>
      <p>Google continues to dominate the camera game. The new "Super Res Zoom Video" allows for crisp 20x zoom in video recordings, and the low-light performance has been significantly improved with AI-enhanced HDR+.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="performance">
      <h2>Performance</h2>
      <p>The Tensor G5 is finally manufactured on a 3nm process, putting it in the same league as Apple's A-series chips in terms of efficiency. It runs cooler and handles multitasking without breaking a sweat.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="battery">
      <h2>Power Management</h2>
      <p>With a 5,100mAh battery and the efficient G5 chip, the Pixel 10 Pro easily lasts over 30 hours on a single charge. The "Adaptive Battery" feature now predicts your usage patterns with 95% accuracy.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="verdict">
      <h2>Verdict</h2>
      <p>If you want the smartest phone on the market, the Pixel 10 Pro is it. It's the perfect showcase for Google's vision of the future. While the hardware is great, the software experience is what truly sets it apart.</p>
      
      <div class="buy-links">
        <h3>Where to Buy</h3>
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/GOOGLEPIXEL10?tag=rc0440-20" class="buy-btn" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">
          Check Price on Amazon
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .review {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: white;
  }

  .review-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .category {
    background: #4285F4;
    color: white;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .review-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .meta {
    color: #666;
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .rating {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: #f8f9fa;
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .score {
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #4285F4;
  }

  .stars {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-left: 1rem;
  }

  .toc {
    background: #f8f9fa;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .toc h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .toc ul {
    list-style: none;
  }

  .toc li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
  }

  .toc a {
    color: #4285F4;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  section h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #333;
  }

  section p {
    color: #555;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .pros-cons {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .pros, .cons {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .pros {
    background: #e8f5e9;
  }

  .cons {
    background: #ffebee;
  }

  .pros h3, .cons h3 {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .pros ul, .cons ul {
    list-style: none;
  }

  .pros li, .cons li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .buy-links {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: #f8f9fa;
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .buy-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 1rem 3rem;
    background: #ff9900;
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .buy-btn:hover {
    background: #e68a00;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .pros-cons {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    
    .review-header h1 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }
  }
</style>
